rComments: Julie came to class and blabbered alot. Her industry-experience stories were the highlight of the course as she worked as an auditor. The course was relatively straight forward and a bit bland. You really gotta just read the textbook and know the slides. Julie didn't really add much to the course.

Julie was a good prof and what i liked about her is that she told us what to focus on for the midterm/final. The course is super hard so do ALL the homework and ASK questions when you are confused! She can go a bit fast sometimes and may forget to ask the class if they understand the madness she just taught. It's really the content. not the prof
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Test heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]
